Common IOS commands:

enable		// go from user exec mode to privileged exec mode
reload		// reboot
show running-config
show start-config
copy running-config start-config

show version
show histroy
show users
show clock
show hosts
show sessions

show terminal
terminal length 40      // set IOS page size
terminal length 0	// no paging
terminal width 80

show interface e0

banner motd #message#
banner exec #message#
banner login #message#
banner incoming #message#

--------------------------

# To change timeout from privileged mode:
line con 0
exec-timeout 0 0    // never timeout 
exec-timeout 0 1    // timeout in 1 sec


# To enable previleged mode passowrd
enable password <PASSWORD>


# To set up vty for login
line vty 0 4
password <PASSWORD>
login           <-- require login


# To find out what neighbors my switch is connected to:
  show cdp neighbors

--------------------------

To set up a vlan:

Use "vlan database" to add to the VLAN database
Do "no shut" on the vlan
Assign IP address and subnet mask: ip address a.b.c.d p.q.r.s


---------------------------
To check multicast route:

show ip mroute



===========================

Kernel code is in /vob/ios/sys/os

COMP_INC is defined in flo_vid under /vob/cisco.comp/make-lib

For example:
    #include COMP_INC(kernel, ios_mem.h)
resolves to: 
    #include "/vob/cisco.comp/kernel/include/ios_mem.h"
The corresponding file is a link to the real header file to be included.

------------------------------

To find out what IP packets are coming into my switch:
show ip cache flow

